The paper deals with the construction of linear codes based on functions over finite fields, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The codes are also used in secret sharing schemes and secure two-party computation, which are topics in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper involves the study of weight distributions of the constructed codes, which is a topic in discrete structures (cs.DS). The codes are constructed using plateaued functions, which are also used in cryptography (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with access structures of secret sharing schemes, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
